Oreo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bburlydorf>BBurlydorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/27/03 5:12:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4605.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Gaudralek vs Windblade etc.</span><hr size=1> Incomplete data on Gaudralek, Sword of the Sky make it seem like it doesn't belong on the list. It belongs on the list because it has very decent DPS, a 179 unresistable DD, PLUS a 1 Push Back (knockback).<br>
<br>
I use it with Ingenuity and Punishing Blade AA abilities and am quite happy with it as an aggro weapon. 358 unresistable Critical Blasts, up to 500 Critical Hits, extra swings, and the fact it's a 2Hndr help make it worth using. If I wear my Garish Head Dress (25AC +10% Taunt), use my Taunt Button, and toss in a few right-clicks with a Crystalline Silk Web I will have Aggro.<br>
<br>
I also have a TSBS (which you may note has better DPS than Gaudralek - simular to Windblade). It is my non-aggro weapon.<br>
<br>
Windblade, TSBS, Kreizenn's Flame, Fleshgrinder, etc. are all decent weapons. In grouping situations they may very well allow you to hold aggro. They are however not Aggro Weapons and do not belong on this list.<br>
